ğŸ” Whatâ€™s Happening in Simple Terms

1ï¸âƒ£ Try placing a queen in each row, one per row.
2ï¸âƒ£ If itâ€™s safe â†’ move to next row.
3ï¸âƒ£ If you canâ€™t place anywhere â†’ go back to previous row and try a new spot (backtracking).
4ï¸âƒ£ Continue until all queens are placed.

ğŸ’¡ Key Concepts Learned
Concept	Meaning
Backtracking	Trying all possibilities step by step, and going back if a path fails.
Recursive Function	Function calling itself to handle smaller parts of the same problem.
Base Case	When all rows are filled â€” print solution.
is_safe()	Prevents attacking queens (same column or diagonals).
